      "writtenOn": "2020-05-11T14:10:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think splitting the caching out to a separate CL makes sense. In my experience with composited content from chrome, the image filters are usually static; they may just be moving around on the page, or in a separate layer. From this standpoint, the cached kernel would be beneficial, but it definitely doesn\u0027t make sense for an animating kernel. I don\u0027t have numbers to back up my impressions on content either, so being able to see perf numbers for both cases would be good.",
      "parentUuid": "b334b5bf_8efeb589",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 124,
        "startChar": 0,
